results.name: Dispersion of the complement of row 1 of A056536.
comment: Rectangular array read by antidiagonals; a permutation of the natural numbers. (Row 1) = squares = A000290(n) = n^2. (Dispersion of complement of column 1 of A082156) = (Transpose of A056537).  The associated fractal sequence is A122196.
link: C. Kimberling, Interspersions and dispersions, Proceedings of the American Mathematical Society, 117 (1993) 313-321.
Clark Kimberling and John E. Brown, Partial Complements and Transposable Dispersions, J. Integer Seqs., Vol. 7, 2004.
results.author: _Clark Kimberling_, Apr 05 2003
